            <div class="card">
              <div class="card-main">
                <div class="card-img">
                  <img alt="alt text" src="images/samples/landscape.jpg">
                  <p class="card-img-heading">
                    ROBO MAZE
                  </p>
                </div>
                <div class="card-inner">
                  <section class="content-inner">
                    <h2 class="content-sub-heading">
                      ROBO MAZE
                    </h2>
                    <p>
                      <a class="btn collapsed waves-attach waves-button"
                      data-toggle="collapse" href=
                      "me#collapsible-region-2"><span class=
											"collapsed-hide"><i class="fa fa-eye-slash"></i> hide</span><span class=
											"collapsed-show"><i class="fa fa-eye"></i> view</span></a>
                    </p>
                    <div class="collapsible-region collapse" id=
                    "collapsible-region-2">
                      <div>
                        
                        <p id="desc">
                          Trust ROBO; Trust yourself; Find the best way "One,
                          who falls behind, is left behind." So pack your bags
                          and pump your bots ‘cause it's get, set and GO!!!<br>
                          TASK:<br>
                          Design a robot either wired or wireless within the
                          specified dimensions that can travel through all
                          turns of the track. The robot that will complete the
                          specified task taking minimum time (within the given
                          time limit) will secure the 1st and 2nd positions
                          resp. will be the winner.
                        </p>
                        <p></p>
                        <p id="rules">
                          Rules
                        </p>GENERAL RULES:<br>
                        • This is racing event, so fastest and most balanced
                        robot will win.<br>
                        • Robot should be as per the given specifications.<br>
                        • Each team can have maximum two members.<br>
                        • Each member of the team must contain the identity
                        card of his/her respected institute.<br>
                        • The robot should not damage the arena.<br>
                        • The competition is based on time trail system<br>
                        • Your robot must be ready when call is made for your
                        team.<br>
                        • Machine must not contain any pneumatic & hydraulic
                        systems, IC engines.<br>
                        • Decision about your robot will be taken by the
                        co-ordinators.<br>
                        • No team will get a second chance after completing the
                        track with poor score.<br>
                        • Decision of judges will be final.<br>
                        • Certificates of Participation will be given to all
                        the teams that will participate in the event.
                        <p></p>
                        <p></p>
                        <p id="prize">
                          Prize
                        </p>FIRST PRIZE : 3000/-<br>
                        SECOND PRIZE: 2000/-
                        <p></p>
                        <p></p>
                        <p id="otherdetails">
                          Other Details
                        </p>ROBOT SPECIFICATIONS:<br>
                        • The maximum dimension of the robot can be 30 x 30 x
                        30 cm (l x b x h).<br>
                        • The robot may be wired or wireless.<br>
                        • The length of the wire (for wired bots) should be at
                        least 4 meter<br>
                        • Maximum of 12 Volt potential can be used.<br>
                        • Readymade toy cars are not allowed.<br>
                        TRACK SPECIFICATION:<br>
                        • The track surface and course line may have
                        unevenness.<br>
                        • There might be abrupt angles.<br>
                        • There will be certain obstacles in the race track
                        which will try to slow down the robot.<br>
                        • Checkpoints will be present at certain places on the
                        track.<br>
                        <br>
                        DATE & TIME : 12.00 PM – 4.00 PM, 22/09/2015<br>
                        VENUE : VOLLEY-BALL COURT
                        <p></p>
                      </div>
                    </div>
                  </section>
                </div>
